codex
Implemented a concrete refactor fix in the new sync path. [sync-node.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-sync/src/sync-node.ts#L197) now supports silent hydration via `notifyListeners: false` in `fetchMessages()` and `insertMessage()`, and [syncBridge.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-cli/src/api/syncBridge.ts#L105) uses that on connect so resumed session processes hydrate transcript state without replaying old user prompts into the live agent queue. I also fixed the server-side token-claims schema import for the `tsx` standalone runtime in [syncNodeToken.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-server/sources/app/auth/syncNodeToken.ts#L1).

Added regression coverage in [sync-node.test.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-sync/src/sync-node.test.ts#L633) and [sync-node.integration.test.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-sync/src/sync-node.integration.test.ts#L847).

Verified with:
- `yarn workspace @slopus/happy-sync test:unit`
- `yarn workspace @slopus/happy-sync test:integration`
- `yarn workspace happy-coder build`
- `yarn workspace happy-server build`

I also ran the full CLI suite. It still has one unrelated failing test in [openclaw.integration.test.ts](/Users/kirilldubovitskiy/projects/happy/.dev/worktree/happy-sync-refactor/packages/happy-cli/src/openclaw/openclaw.integration.test.ts#L286): the backend response assertion expects `"backend test ok"` but got `"hello from happy test"`. The full refactor document is not complete yet; the remaining work is still the larger legacy ACP/OpenClaw/app path removal.
